10. imperfitfirem: military authority (imperium) could, strictly speaking, be conferred only by a special law. It became customary, however, to use the word impertitor as a title of honor. Soldiers sometimes bestowed it on their general after a successful battle. Julius Caesar and nearly all of his successors prefixed it to their names ; hence the title of emperor.
